# Deny-all; allowlist exactly what docker/Dockerfile COPYs (context is the repo root
# for both CI and docker-compose). .env, .git, node_modules, dist must never reach the
# docker daemon — a future `COPY . .` would otherwise bake secrets into a shipped layer.
*
!package.json
!bun.lock
!apps/console/package.json
!packages
!services/worker
# nested junk inside the allowlisted trees
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.env*
**/*.test.ts
